University affiliation status.

The rank of an affiliated university was correlated against the five video popularity indicators. Universities outside of the top 200 (according to the Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2011–12) were allocated a joint last rank (201). No significant differences (at the p = 0.05 level) were found ( Table 7 ).
